---
description:
Networking standards using Dio.

alwaysApply: true
---

# Networking

LexMastery uses Dio.

Never use:

http package

direct sockets

raw REST clients

---

# API Layer

Networking follows:

Controller

↓

Repository

↓

Datasource

↓

Dio Client

Widgets never call APIs.

---

# Base Client

Create one shared Dio client.

Location:

core/network/

Responsibilities:

- base URL
- headers
- interceptors
- timeout
- retries

---

# Authentication

Inject JWT automatically.

Never manually attach Authorization headers.

---

# Timeouts

Configure:

connect

receive

send

timeouts.

Avoid infinite waits.

---

# Interceptors

Implement:

Authentication

Logging

Retry

Refresh Token

Error Mapping

Analytics (future)

---

# Logging

Enable detailed logs only in development.

Never log:

JWT

Passwords

PII

Tokens

---

# DTOs

Every endpoint has:

Request DTO

Response DTO

Never deserialize directly into domain models.

---

# Mapping

DTO

↓

Mapper

↓

Domain Model

Never skip mapping.

---

# Error Mapping

Convert:

Timeout

401

403

404

409

422

500

Network Failure

into domain failures.

---

# Cancellation

Cancel obsolete requests.

Especially:

Search

AI Streaming

Pagination

---

# File Uploads

Use multipart.

Track upload progress.

Support cancellation.

---

# Downloads

Support:

resume

retry

cancel

progress

---

# Streaming

AI endpoints should support streaming.

Use incremental updates.

Never wait for entire response.

---

# Retry Policy

Retry only idempotent requests.

Never retry:

payments

mutations

exam submissions

---

# Cursor Instructions

Always generate:

Datasource

DTOs

Mapper

Repository

Tests

Never call Dio from controllers.